<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Cursor Rules</title>
    <style>
        /* CSS Architecture */
        body {
            background-color: #F8F8F8; /* Light Gray */
            color: #333;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 0;
        }

        h1, h2, h3 {
            color: #10A4FF; /* Bright Blue */
        }

        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .btn {
            background-color: #0097F5; /* Medium Blue */
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: #0065A3; /* Dark Teal Blue */
        }

        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            body {
                padding: 10px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Cursor Rules</h1>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>This document outlines the cursor rules and best practices for development.</p>

    <h2>HTML Standards</h2>
    <p>Adhere to the following HTML standards:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Always include a doctype.</li>
        <li>Use semantic HTML whenever possible.</li>
        <li>Ensure accessibility by using proper ARIA labels.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>CSS Architecture</h2>
    <p>Follow these CSS architecture practices:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Keep styles modular and reusable.</li>
        <li>Utilize BEM (Block Element Modifier) methodology.</li>
        <li>Organize styles in a way that promotes maintainability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Responsive Design</h2>
    <p>Ensure your designs are responsive:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Use fluid grids and flexible images.</li>
        <li>Implement media queries for different screen sizes.</li>
        <li>Test designs on various devices.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Development Best Practices</h2>
    <p>Follow these best practices for development:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Write clean and well-documented code.</li>
        <li>Use version control systems.</li>
        <li>Perform code reviews regularly.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Maser Media COLORWAY Palette</h2>
    <p>Here are the colors of our updated Maser Media COLORWAY palette:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Light Gray: <span style="color:#F8F8F8">#F8F8F8</span></li>
        <li>Bright Blue: <span style="color:#10A4FF">#10A4FF</span></li>
        <li>Medium Blue: <span style="color:#0097F5">#0097F5</span></li>
        <li>Dark Teal Blue: <span style="color:#0065A3">#0065A3</span></li>
    </ul>
</body>
</html>
